  "brief_justification": "This is a qualitative International Relations article that analyzes two WTO dispute cases (pharmaceutical patents and cotton subsidies) to argue that democratic institutional improvements in Brazilian foreign policy formulation can enhance diplomatic quality and international credibility. The paper uses comparative case studies with no quantitative data analysis, no tables, figures, or equations, and relies on documentary and journalistic sources. It has no explicit method section and follows an essayistic analytical style."
